[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2451009352","html_url":"https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/53509#issuecomment-2451009352","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/53509","id":2451009352,"node_id":"IC_kwDNIULOkhdvSA","user":{"login":"ibrahima","id":47774,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3Nzc0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47774?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima","html_url":"https://github.com/ibrahima","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-10-31T23:21:24Z","updated_at":"2024-10-31T23:22:23Z","body":"Hi! I've just noticed a similar issue with `select` - if I have a table alias and reference the aliased table in a `where` call, the alias is applied, but if not, then it uses the original table name. This makes conditionally chaining queries annoying depending on what conditions are applied. E.g. in my application, I have different filters applied to a query depending on the user, and then I `select` some additional fields onto the object from the joined relations, but I have to reference the joined table with different names depending on whether the table was referenced in the `where` clauses.\r\n\r\nIn this test case, I have two models, Post, and PostComment, but the relation on Post is just called `comments`. If I add the `where` clause then I can include the joined table fields using the `comments` alias, but otherwise I have to use the original `post_comments` table name.\r\n\r\nI'm seeing this on Rails 7.2.1.\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n# frozen_string_literal: true\r\n\r\nrequire \"bundler/inline\"\r\n\r\ngemfile(true) do\r\n  source \"https://rubygems.org\"\r\n\r\n  gem \"rails\"\r\n  # If you want to test against edge Rails replace the previous line with this:\r\n  # gem \"rails\", github: \"rails/rails\", branch: \"main\"\r\n\r\n  gem \"sqlite3\"\r\nend\r\n\r\nrequire \"active_record\"\r\nrequire \"minitest/autorun\"\r\nrequire \"logger\"\r\n\r\n# This connection will do for database-independent bug reports.\r\nActiveRecord::Base.establish_connection(adapter: \"sqlite3\", database: \":memory:\")\r\nActiveRecord::Base.logger = Logger.new(STDOUT)\r\n\r\nActiveRecord::Schema.define do\r\n  create_table :posts, force: true do |t|\r\n    t.string :title\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  create_table :post_comments, force: true do |t|\r\n    t.string :title\r\n    t.integer :post_id\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass Post < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n  has_many :comments, class_name: \"PostComment\"\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass PostComment < ActiveRecord::Base\r\n  belongs_to :post\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass BugTest < ActiveSupport::TestCase\r\n  def test_association_stuff\r\n    post = Post.create!(title: \"Hello\")\r\n    post.comments << (comment_1 = PostComment.create!(title: \"Hello, comment\"))\r\n\r\n    post_2 = Post.create!(title: \"World\")\r\n    post_2.comments << (comment_2 = PostComment.create!(title: \"World, comment\"))\r\n\r\n    # WORKS\r\n    assert_equal [post, post_2], Post.joins(:comments).where.not(comments: { title: nil }).select(posts: [\"*\"], comments: [\"title as comment\"])\r\n\r\n    # BROKEN... `comments` alias isn't set\r\n    assert_equal [post, post_2], Post.joins(:comments).select(posts: [\"*\"], comments: [\"title as comment\"])\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```","author_association":"NONE"