ima/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-11-02T00:16:38Z","updated_at":"2024-11-02T00:20:13Z","body":"@kamipo by the way, it seems like the latest changes on `main` have broken my [similar test case](https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/53509#issuecomment-2451009352) further - now it turns `select(posts: [\"*\"])` into `SELECT \"posts\".\"*\"` instead of `SELECT posts.*` which fails because `\"*\"` is not a column name. Now, I don't know if it was ever intended for `select` to work that way, I was kind of pleasantly surprised when I wrote that query and it worked, but just wanted to mention it in case that's something that should still be working. Thank you!\r\n\r\nEdit: Ah yeah, even if I remove that \"posts\".\"*\" bit I'm seeing that the other part of the select also no longer works because it's quoted. So maybe we're just not meant to be able to do that with a hash argument to `select` and it was lucky coincidence that it wasn't quoting that column name so that we could do more complex things with it.\r\n\r\nActiveRecord::StatementInvalid: SQLite3::SQLException: no such column: comments.title as comment:\r\n```sql\r\nSELECT \"comments\".\"title as comment\" FROM \"posts\" INNER JOIN \"post_comments\" \"comments\" ON \"comments\".\"post_id\" = \"posts\".\"id\"\r\n```","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2452746340/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ibrahima","id":47774,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3Nzc0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47774?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima","html_url":"https://github.com/ibrahima","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ibrahima/following{/other